Hello.

01:11.801 --> 01:14.135
<i>Dad, it's me.
What's up? It's Amy.</i>

01:14.136 --> 01:15.637
What's wrong?

01:15.638 --> 01:17.739
Amy, what time is it?

01:17.740 --> 01:19.607
Uh, it's 7 here.

01:19.608 --> 01:21.242
Amy, it's 4:00 in the morning.

01:21.243 --> 01:23.411
I know, but I don't know
how to get to where I'm going.

01:23.412 --> 01:24.579
Get a taxi.

01:24.580 --> 01:25.914
I don't think
we're supposed to do that.

01:25.915 --> 01:27.248
The instructions say
to take a subway,

01:27.249 --> 01:29.284
but I don't know
where I can find a subway.

01:29.285 --> 01:30.785
Oh, I'm sure you can find it,

01:30.786 --> 01:32.954
but you need to leave
your apartment and go outside.

01:32.955 --> 01:34.656
I know.

01:34.657 --> 01:36.958
But it's so nice in here.
[laughs]

01:36.959 --> 01:38.293
Did I tell you
I have a kitchen?

01:38.294 --> 01:39.961
Your dad told me.

01:39.962 --> 01:41.930
Do you need to be somewhere
at a certain time, Amy?

01:41.931 --> 01:44.098
I just have to register today.

01:44.099 --> 01:45.767
How do I pay for the subway?

01:45.768 --> 01:46.968
You buy a MetroCard.

01:46.969 --> 01:48.136
Where do I buy that?

01:48.137 --> 01:50.872
Amy, we went over all this
before you left.

01:50.873 --> 01:53.141
You buy MetroCards
in the subway station.

01:53.142 --> 01:54.642
Do you have your map?

01:54.643 --> 01:56.744
The subway stations
are marked on the map.

01:56.745 --> 01:59.414
It's really easy to find
your way around there.
It's on a grid.

01:59.415 --> 02:02.717
All right.
Well, wish me luck.

02:02.718 --> 02:04.652
Good luck, Amy.

02:04.653 --> 02:06.454
Are you okay?

02:06.455 --> 02:09.757
I guess. I mean,
I love my apartment.

02:09.758 --> 02:12.594
Dorm room.
Your dad wants you
to call it a dorm room,

02:12.595 --> 02:13.928
so call it that.

02:13.929 --> 02:15.930
He'll sleep a lot easier

02:15.931 --> 02:17.599
and so will I,

02:17.600 --> 02:19.901
especially if you don't call
at 4 in the morning, okay?

02:19.902 --> 02:22.303
All right.
Have a nice day.

02:22.304 --> 02:23.638
You, too, Amy.

02:23.639 --> 02:25.840
You have a good
first day in New York.

02:25.841 --> 02:27.442
And you'll be fine.

02:27.443 --> 02:28.943
New Yorkers are really friendly,

02:28.944 --> 02:30.945
and they're used
to seeing people lost.

02:30.946 --> 02:32.280
They'll help you
if you need help.

02:32.281 --> 02:34.115
You can help yourself
just by looking at a map.

02:34.116 --> 02:35.950
All right.
Bye, Mom.

02:35.951 --> 02:37.919
Bye, honey.

02:37.920 --> 02:39.020
