If this ever happened to you,
you'd tell me, right?

12:17.206 --> 12:18.840
Truthfully, I'm not sure.

12:18.841 --> 12:20.341
And don't take that
the wrong way.

12:20.342 --> 12:21.909
If you know,
you'd tell Ben,

12:21.910 --> 12:24.178
and he'd tell Grace,
and she'd tell Jack,

12:24.179 --> 12:26.080
and he'd tell Madison,

12:26.081 --> 12:28.182
and even though
she wouldn't mean to,
she'd tell everyone.

12:28.183 --> 12:30.551
Then we're just not going
to have sex again until
we're married.

12:32.955 --> 12:34.188
I would tell you,
all right?

12:34.189 --> 12:35.556
All right.

12:35.557 --> 12:37.592
Don't threaten me again,

12:37.593 --> 12:39.327
especially for
just being honest.

12:39.328 --> 12:41.496
And I'm being honest when
I tell you I'd want to know.

12:41.497 --> 12:44.666
Let's not get into any fights
about a hypothetical situation.

12:44.667 --> 12:46.801
Okay, but maybe we should

12:46.802 --> 12:49.170
talk about these hypothetical
situations some more.

12:49.171 --> 12:51.639
Odds are,
as careful as we are,
it's never gonna happen.

12:51.640 --> 12:53.608
If it does happen,

12:53.609 --> 12:55.576
I want you to have the baby,

12:55.577 --> 12:57.078
and I wanna get married.

13:00.049 --> 13:01.849
Let's just see
that it doesn't happen.

13:13.295 --> 13:16.297
I'm here for
a job interview.

13:16.298 --> 13:18.633
Yes. So am I.

13:18.634 --> 13:20.968
What kind of work
do you do?

13:20.969 --> 13:24.172
I was a vice president
of a company

13:24.173 --> 13:26.874
that was basically bribing
congressional members

13:26.875 --> 13:29.577
to vote in such a way that would
increase our profit margin.

13:29.578 --> 13:30.912
Interesting.

13:30.913 --> 13:32.714
Don't know what it means,

13:32.715 --> 13:35.183
but interesting.
[chuckles]

13:35.184 --> 13:38.820
I was there for 28 years
till a scandal shut down
the company,

13:38.821 --> 13:40.822
leaving me unemployed,

13:40.823 --> 13:43.458
which is basically
why my wife left me.

13:43.459 --> 13:44.659
Did you go to jail?

13:44.660 --> 13:46.661
No. No.

13:46.662 --> 13:49.964
I wasn't even
remotely involved.

13:49.965 --> 13:51.966
Maybe remotely.

13:51.967 --> 13:54.202
Uh, what, uh--
What job are you applying for?

13:54.203 --> 13:55.303
Mail room.

13:55.304 --> 13:57.872
Ah. Me, too.

13:57.873 --> 14:01.142
My girlfriend is pregnant.

14:01.143 --> 14:03.010
I need this job.

14:03.011 --> 14:05.413
So is mine.

14:06.849 --> 14:08.116
Look, kid,

14:08.117 --> 14:10.051
you're not gonna get
the sympathy vote from me, okay?

14:10.052 --> 14:12.086
'Cause I can match you
trouble for trouble.

14:12.087 --> 14:14.222
Then may the best man win.

14:14.223 --> 14:15.523
Let's go.

14:15.524 --> 14:16.958
Bring it on, dawg.

14:19.895 --> 14:21.629
I think I just need
to go home.

14:21.630 --> 14:23.831
My mind is really not
on my work today.

14:23.832 --> 14:26.968
You can't.
I've covered for you
enough lately.

14:26.969 --> 14:28.970
Besides, what are you
gonna do at home?

14:28.971 --> 14:30.705
There's nothing
you can do.

14:30.706 --> 14:34.809
I know, but...
I don't wanna be here.

14:34.810 --> 14:36.878
I don't wanna be at home.

14:36.879 --> 14:38.946
I don't know
what I want...

14:38.947 --> 14:41.382
other than for Amy
never to find out.

14:41.383 --> 14:42.917
Is that why you're
going along with this?

14:42.918 --> 14:44.919
Because you think you can
hide this from Amy?

14:44.920 --> 14:46.854
You can't hide this
from Amy.

14:46.855 --> 14:49.757
I mean, for all you know,
one day, when Adrian's temper
gets the best of her again,

14:49.758 --> 14:51.459
she'll tell Amy.

14:52.761 --> 14:55.096
Hey, if you're just
agreeing to an abortion

14:55.097 --> 14:58.566
because you don't want anyone
to ever find out Adrian
was pregnant,

14:58.567 --> 15:00.234
think again, my friend.

15:00.235 --> 15:02.703
It's not gonna happen.
I'm not agreeing
to anything,

15:02.704 --> 15:04.705
I don't think.

15:04.706 --> 15:08.109
But you're for abortion,
right?

15:08.110 --> 15:09.777
"For"?

15:09.778 --> 15:11.779
I'm not for abortion.

15:11.780 --> 15:13.781
But I'm not against abortion.

15:13.782 --> 15:15.650
And what I'm really for

15:15.651 --> 15:17.251
is the mom
and the dad deciding

15:17.252 --> 15:19.220
before the baby is born.

15:19.221 --> 15:22.824
It's better to decide
before you have the kid
than after.

15:22.825 --> 15:26.494
My parents pretty much decided
I shouldn't have been born
after I was born.

15:31.366 --> 15:34.469
Look, Ben, if you and Adrian
don't want Adrian to have
the baby

15:34.470 --> 15:36.704
because you don't want
Amy to find out,

15:36.705 --> 15:38.706
then that's probably
not a good reason,

15:38.707 --> 15:40.608
if you're looking
for a reason.

15:40.609 --> 15:42.610
We don't have a reason.

15:42.611 --> 15:44.111
We just don't want a baby.

15:44.112 --> 15:46.214
Neither of us wants a baby.

15:46.215 --> 15:48.316
But I don't know if Adrian
having an abortion

15:48.317 --> 15:49.984
is the right thing
or the wrong thing.

15:49.985 --> 15:52.053
I honestly don't.
Stop judging, okay?

15:52.054 --> 15:54.922
Just go with what is
and stop judging.

15:54.923 --> 15:57.425
You don't know if something bad
will come of this,

15:57.426 --> 16:00.228
or something good will come
of not going through
with the pregnancy.

16:00.229 --> 16:02.964
I mean, maybe it's a future
Mother Teresa that's not
gonna be born,

16:02.965 --> 16:06.334
or maybe it's a future Hitler
that's not gonna be born.

16:06.335 --> 16:08.102
No one knows.
You can't know.

16:08.103 --> 16:10.204
Well, what's
the right thing to do?

16:10.205 --> 16:12.306
Support her decision
not to have the baby,

16:12.307 --> 16:13.808
or try to talk her out of it?

16:13.809 --> 16:17.512
Try to live with
whatever decision she makes.

16:17.513 --> 16:19.113
All right?

16:19.114 --> 16:22.850
Whatever is, is,
and life goes on.

16:22.851 --> 16:25.520
Or it doesn't.

16:47.727 --> 16:49.728
Hey, let me help you with that.

16:49.729 --> 16:52.864
Big help.
I carry it from upstairs.

16:54.800 --> 16:56.835
I think we should just
tell your mom
I'm living out here

16:56.836 --> 16:58.903
in the guest house with you
until I find somewhere else.

16:58.904 --> 17:00.638
And that way,
I can help you out.

17:00.639 --> 17:03.008
That way,
she will get mad,

17:03.009 --> 17:07.378
and you will get kicked out
of here, buddy.

17:07.380 --> 17:10.080
Well, we're gonna have to
tell her I'm living out here
at some point.

17:10.082 --> 17:12.083
You can't hide me forever.
Too soon.

17:12.084 --> 17:15.286
My truck is parked
a block away in front
of someone else's house.

17:15.287 --> 17:17.821
What if I get towed?
Don't worry.

17:17.823 --> 17:20.525
I working at the courthouse.

17:20.526 --> 17:22.193
Did you get the job?
Is it definite?

17:22.194 --> 17:24.729
I just have to take a test.

17:24.730 --> 17:26.664
An easy one.

17:45.418 --> 17:47.218
[sniffs]

17:55.361 --> 17:57.695
Hey, I can do that.

17:57.696 --> 17:59.431
I just put
the boys to bed.

17:59.432 --> 18:02.000
I got it. You cooked.
I'm happy to clean up.

18:02.001 --> 18:03.334
No.
[chuckles]

18:03.335 --> 18:05.303
I really appreciate you
staying here.

18:05.304 --> 18:07.572
It's what Amy wants,
so I'm happy to do it.

18:07.573 --> 18:09.574
It's really nice of you.

18:09.575 --> 18:12.077
I really appreciate
you being here.

18:12.078 --> 18:14.813
I think getting away
for a few weeks is gonna be
really great for Amy.

18:14.814 --> 18:16.314
I didn't hear
from her today.

18:16.315 --> 18:18.316
I'm sure she's busy
with her first day of school

18:18.317 --> 18:20.752
and finding her way
around New York.

18:20.753 --> 18:23.455
I hope she's okay.
I'm sure she's fine.

18:23.456 --> 18:26.257
Who knows? This might lead
to her going to Juilliard

18:26.258 --> 18:28.126
or maybe playing
for the New York Philharmonic.

18:28.127 --> 18:29.627
I guess.

18:29.628 --> 18:31.629
It's good, right?

18:31.630 --> 18:34.966
You'd have to ask
a French horn player.
I just know sticks.

18:34.967 --> 18:37.435
I don't even know why
she picked the French horn
in the first place.

18:37.436 --> 18:38.670
I know.

18:38.671 --> 18:40.105
You know why she picked
the French horn?

18:40.106 --> 18:42.273
I hate to
bring up band camp,

18:42.274 --> 18:44.142
but she told me the story
at band camp.

18:44.143 --> 18:46.077
Well, John's over a year old.

18:46.078 --> 18:49.047
I think we've gotten past
any resentment from band camp.

18:50.416 --> 18:52.484
<i>It was Peter and the Wolf.</i>

18:52.485 --> 18:55.720
<i>You played
Peter and the Wolf to her
over and over again, right?</i>

18:55.721 --> 18:59.357
Yeah, I did.
The French horn plays
the part of the wolf.

18:59.358 --> 19:02.293
Yeah. She was scared
of the wolf.

19:02.294 --> 19:04.996
She thought
if she became the wolf,
she wouldn't be afraid anymore.

19:04.997 --> 19:06.297
She thought that
in the third grade?

19:06.298 --> 19:08.800
She thought that
in the third grade.

19:08.801 --> 19:10.802
And she thought that
you loved the wolf part

19:10.803 --> 19:12.904
<i>of Peter and the Wolf best.</i>

19:12.905 --> 19:14.839
And she just wanted
you to love her.

19:14.840 --> 19:17.842
But I do love her.
I've always loved her.

19:17.843 --> 19:20.578
She knows that.
Well, she knows that now.

19:29.788 --> 19:31.523
What are you eating?

19:31.524 --> 19:33.024
I'm not sure.

19:33.025 --> 19:36.361
Too frozen to tell,
but I think they're brownies.

19:36.362 --> 19:39.964
So, you eating brownies.

19:39.965 --> 19:44.002
I am doing
alt the heavy lifting.

19:44.003 --> 19:45.937
Give me one of those.

19:54.547 --> 19:56.581
Good, huh?
Mm-hmm.

19:56.582 --> 19:58.082
I just wanted to offer
to go with you.

19:58.083 --> 19:59.417
My mother's going with me.

19:59.418 --> 20:01.920
I could drive us.
Actually, you can't.

20:01.921 --> 20:03.755
You have
a provisional license.

20:03.756 --> 20:05.557
My driver could drive us.

20:05.558 --> 20:08.526
Um, all three of us--
or four, if my dad goes.

20:08.527 --> 20:10.595
Dads aren't going--
mine or yours.

20:10.596 --> 20:12.263
This is very private.

20:12.264 --> 20:14.098
And I would hate
for everyone

20:14.099 --> 20:17.101
to see your dad's car
and driver outside the clinic.

20:17.102 --> 20:20.271
But thanks, Ben.
Thanks for offering.

20:20.272 --> 20:22.273
Adrian, I don't know
what to do here.

20:22.274 --> 20:23.741
I wanna do something.

20:23.742 --> 20:25.510
There's nothing you can do

20:25.511 --> 20:29.180
except maybe be my friend.

20:29.181 --> 20:31.783
Maybe you can
come by on Sunday

20:31.784 --> 20:34.085
and we can just hang out
or something.

20:34.086 --> 20:36.287
I can't go with you?

20:36.288 --> 20:38.256
I mean, shouldn't I
be there with you?

20:38.257 --> 20:40.491
No, it's better if you're not.

20:40.492 --> 20:42.093
I'll talk to you Sunday, okay?

20:42.094 --> 20:44.629
Okay, Adrian.

20:44.630 --> 20:47.765
Um, I'm sorry.

20:47.766 --> 20:49.434
I know, Ben.

20:49.435 --> 20:51.302
Me, too. Good night.

20:51.303 --> 20:54.339
Good night.
[beeps]

20:55.441 --> 20:58.009
[Ruben]
No means no.
I said no.

20:58.010 --> 20:59.510
[Cindy]
You can say no all you want,

20:59.511 --> 21:01.179
but Adrian already
made her decision,

21:01.180 --> 21:03.114
and I'm supporting her.

21:03.115 --> 21:04.449
Well, I'm not.

21:04.450 --> 21:06.584
And I'm her father.
And I didn't come back

21:06.585 --> 21:08.987
into this family
to be excluded
and disrespected.

21:08.988 --> 21:11.356
This is not about you.
This is about Adrian.

21:11.357 --> 21:14.125
Of course it's about Adrian.
I love Adrian.

21:14.126 --> 21:15.593
And I don't want her
to do this.

21:15.594 --> 21:17.595
I think she'll regret this
for the rest of her life.

21:17.596 --> 21:19.097
This was not
an easy decision.

21:19.098 --> 21:22.100
It was not easy,
but it was made easier
because you agreed with her.

21:22.101 --> 21:24.769
That's not true.
I would support her decision
either way.

21:24.770 --> 21:25.970
Did you let her know that?

21:25.971 --> 21:28.706
Of course I did.

21:42.855 --> 21:42.920
What the heck
is going on next door?

21:44.923 --> 21:47.125
People are yelling.
People are saying things--

21:47.126 --> 21:49.160
things that I could hear.
Oh?

21:49.161 --> 21:51.996
Ashley, Adrian is pregnant,
isn't she?

21:51.997 --> 21:53.931
I don't know.

21:53.932 --> 21:55.667
Well, I don't know
if she's still pregnant.

21:55.668 --> 21:58.469
Oh, God.
Does Ben know?

21:58.470 --> 21:59.971
I don't think so.

21:59.972 --> 22:03.141
I don't think she wanted him
to know anything about it.

22:03.142 --> 22:04.976
But he might.

22:04.977 --> 22:06.444
He might?
He might.

22:06.445 --> 22:08.112
Did you know about this
when you encouraged

22:08.113 --> 22:11.149
your sister to go to New York?
I don't really know
anything about it.

22:11.150 --> 22:13.151
I don't wanna know
anything about it. It's--

22:13.152 --> 22:15.286
You know, it's none
of my business.

22:15.287 --> 22:17.455
It's no one's business.
No one's but Adrian's.

22:17.456 --> 22:19.857
This is not good.
Just forget you heard anything.

22:19.858 --> 22:21.859
How?
Okay, don't forget,

22:21.860 --> 22:24.629
but don't say anything
to Mom.

22:24.630 --> 22:27.498
You can't. We can't.
[sighs]

22:27.499 --> 22:29.534
We made a promise
that our lying days are over.

22:29.535 --> 22:31.269
You know, what good is it
gonna do to tell Mom

22:31.270 --> 22:33.871
that Adrian's having an abortion
or had an abortion?

22:33.872 --> 22:37.008
It's really not right
to talk about it at all.
To anyone.

22:37.009 --> 22:38.543
[knocks]

22:40.079 --> 22:43.081
Hi. Sorry to interrupt,
but the little fella's awake,

22:43.082 --> 22:45.783
and I think Mrs. Juergens
is in the shower
or something.

22:45.784 --> 22:47.985
Thanks, Ricky.
I'll take him.

22:47.986 --> 22:49.487
Hey, buddy.

22:49.488 --> 22:50.922
Whoa.

22:54.927 --> 22:56.661
[sighs]

23:01.533 --> 23:04.202
What's going on?
I don't know.

23:04.203 --> 23:05.203
Yeah, you do.

23:05.204 --> 23:07.238
Yeah, I do. Um...

23:07.239 --> 23:09.273
but I don't want
to talk about it.

23:09.274 --> 23:11.242
All right.

23:11.243 --> 23:13.578
Well, I guess
I'll just say good night.

23:16.014 --> 23:17.382
Should I say good night?

23:25.691 --> 23:27.191
Tell me what's wrong.

23:27.192 --> 23:29.494
Does it ever go right?

23:29.495 --> 23:31.696
Does the right girl
ever find the right guy?

23:31.697 --> 23:33.231
Sure.

23:35.634 --> 23:36.667
Sure?

23:36.668 --> 23:37.835
Yeah.

23:37.836 --> 23:39.737
Sure. It can happen.

23:43.008 --> 23:45.743
No, we can't.
We can't, Ashley.

23:45.744 --> 23:49.781
- We can if we want.
- No, we can't.

24:29.817 --> 24:31.351
Where is she?

24:31.352 --> 24:32.853
I don't know.

24:32.854 --> 24:34.221
She said she had to get out.

24:34.222 --> 24:35.856
She couldn't take us
arguing anymore.

24:35.857 --> 24:37.357
She'll be home tomorrow.

24:37.358 --> 24:38.892
Tomorrow!

24:38.893 --> 24:40.894
She's probably gonna try
and take care of this
on her own.

24:42.697 --> 24:44.698
This is your fault,
you know that?

24:44.699 --> 24:46.433
So you find her.

25:02.750 --> 25:04.784
[ringing]

25:06.988 --> 25:08.688
It's Grace.

25:08.689 --> 25:09.890
Hang up.

25:09.891 --> 25:11.358
I haven't answered yet.

25:11.359 --> 25:13.627
Answer it, then hang up.

25:15.897 --> 25:17.564
[beeps]
Hello.

25:17.565 --> 25:19.566
Hi.

25:19.567 --> 25:23.403
Hope I'm not bothering you.
Are you with Madison?

25:23.404 --> 25:25.338
Am I with Madison?

25:25.339 --> 25:27.274
No, I'm not with Madison.
Are you with Madison?

25:28.943 --> 25:30.877
No. Why would I ask you

25:30.878 --> 25:32.879
if you're with Madison
if I was with Madison?

25:32.880 --> 25:35.282
I don't know.

25:35.283 --> 25:37.217
I'm really worried
about Adrian,

25:37.218 --> 25:39.219
and I'm worried
that if I don't say something,

25:39.220 --> 25:41.721
I'm going to hell,
and you're going with me.

25:41.722 --> 25:42.956
All right.

25:42.957 --> 25:45.258
"All right"?
What is wrong with you?

25:45.259 --> 25:48.228
I'm not sure.
I'll call you back.

25:48.229 --> 25:49.162
[beeps]

25:55.403 --> 25:58.905
Tom, who was the last guest
to stay in this guest house?

25:58.906 --> 26:00.640
Gut house.

26:00.641 --> 26:02.142
Guest house.

26:02.143 --> 26:03.877
Guest of the guest house.
Guest of the guest house.

26:03.878 --> 26:05.879
Shoo, fly, shoo.

26:05.880 --> 26:07.447
Ow. My darlin'.

26:07.448 --> 26:09.783
[chuckling]

26:11.619 --> 26:13.586
Tom, I think we're high.

26:13.587 --> 26:15.555
I think these are
marijuana brownies.

26:15.556 --> 26:17.223
Better not be.

26:17.224 --> 26:22.262
I have a drug test
on Monday at the courthouse.

26:22.263 --> 26:25.532
That was the test--
the easy test?

26:25.533 --> 26:27.867
[sighs]
It's not gonna be
so easy anymore.

26:30.104 --> 26:33.239
I don't feel so well.

26:33.240 --> 26:36.810
I don't feel well either.

26:36.811 --> 26:38.812
Worst news for you,

26:38.813 --> 26:40.880
there's only one bathroom.

26:45.953 --> 26:47.053
[sighs]

26:49.957 --> 26:51.791
Where you going?

26:51.792 --> 26:53.126
To take Moose for a walk.

26:53.127 --> 26:54.461
He already had a walk.

26:54.462 --> 26:56.796
I think he needs
to go out again.
You sure?

26:56.797 --> 26:58.999
Well, not totally sure.

27:03.604 --> 27:05.705
Well, you could either
take Moose for a walk

27:05.706 --> 27:08.041
or we could just
go to bed.

27:09.143 --> 27:11.978
But we were in bed
just this morning.

27:11.979 --> 27:13.113
Uh-huh.

27:13.114 --> 27:14.514
It's either feast
or famine with you.

27:14.515 --> 27:16.883
Are you complaining?
No, no, no, no, no.
Not complaining.

27:18.519 --> 27:20.120
[beeping]

27:22.823 --> 27:24.424
[ringing]

27:27.528 --> 27:28.962
[beeps]

27:30.631 --> 27:32.232
[beeping]

27:33.300 --> 27:35.702
[ringing]
Hey, are you okay?

27:35.703 --> 27:37.237
It's not Adrian.

27:37.238 --> 27:39.539
It's me, Ruben.
Have you seen Adrian?

27:39.540 --> 27:41.608
What do you mean?
I mean, is she over there?

27:41.609 --> 27:43.143
No, she's not over here.

27:43.144 --> 27:45.278
You'd tell me if she
was over there, right?

27:45.279 --> 27:47.347
Even if she told you not to
tell me she was over there?

27:47.348 --> 27:49.149
She's not over here,
I swear.

27:49.150 --> 27:50.650
Okay.

27:50.651 --> 27:52.819
Well, if you see her,
tell her to call me.

27:52.820 --> 27:54.954
Or tell her
to call her mother.
All right.

27:56.023 --> 27:57.190
