Well, I'm just gonna
turn off my computer.

36:30.706 --> 36:33.341
I was just gonna send
something to my family.

36:33.375 --> 36:35.209
Do you have a son
or a daughter?

36:35.244 --> 36:37.812
I have a son.
Me, too.

36:40.382 --> 36:43.484
Um, how did you know
I had a baby?

36:43.519 --> 36:46.320
[chuckles]
And you have a son?

36:46.355 --> 36:48.322
We're all teen moms
and musicians.

36:48.357 --> 36:51.492
Everyone in this program?
The program--
it's for teen moms.

36:51.527 --> 36:54.095
So I didn't get here
on my own?

36:54.129 --> 36:55.930
Of course you did.

36:55.964 --> 36:59.634
You're the world's greatest
French horn player,
and I'm Yo-Yo Ma.

36:59.668 --> 37:01.135
Come on.
We have to get going.

37:06.508 --> 37:08.443
Bink.

37:09.344 --> 37:10.778
[sighs]

37:11.713 --> 37:13.514
You know what?

37:13.549 --> 37:15.917
[sighs]
It's too early to talk.

37:15.951 --> 37:20.154
Last night, Ricky told me
why Amy plays the French horn.

37:20.189 --> 37:22.690
<i>Because of Peter and the Wolf.</i>

37:22.724 --> 37:24.826
<i>Remember Peter and the Wolf?</i>

37:24.860 --> 37:27.395
Yeah, I remember.

37:27.429 --> 37:28.696
Kind of.

37:28.730 --> 37:31.466
Well, that's why Amy
picked the French horn.

37:31.500 --> 37:34.669
It's because she wanted
to get over being scared
of the wolf,

37:34.703 --> 37:37.171
and she wanted me
to love her.

37:37.206 --> 37:38.706
What time is it?

37:38.740 --> 37:40.141
George, are you listening?

37:40.175 --> 37:41.442
Yeah.

37:41.477 --> 37:44.378
I'm really happy that Ricky
decided to stay here.

37:44.413 --> 37:47.048
It'll give us a chance
to get to know him better.

37:47.082 --> 37:49.484
I think he might be
a nice guy after all.

37:50.886 --> 37:52.887
I know that Amy's in love
with Ben right now.

37:52.921 --> 37:54.155
But you never know.

37:54.189 --> 37:56.357
They're young.
Things might change.

37:56.391 --> 37:59.994
Yeah. Things may change,
all right.

38:06.068 --> 38:07.735
[ringing]

38:11.340 --> 38:12.740
[beeps]
Hello.

38:12.774 --> 38:14.609
Where are you?

38:14.643 --> 38:16.577
Um, in the shower.

38:16.612 --> 38:18.346
Can I call you back?

38:18.380 --> 38:21.749
No. And I don't hear
any water running.
I'll call you back.

38:21.783 --> 38:24.886
I was parked behind
your stupid truck
for two hours last night.

38:24.920 --> 38:27.722
Why?
Well, because I was driving
over to Lauren's house,

38:27.756 --> 38:31.092
and I saw your car parked
in front of some girl's house.

38:31.126 --> 38:33.027
What girl?
What do you mean,
"What girl?"

38:33.061 --> 38:35.463
Look, you're not
gonna be happy with this.

38:35.497 --> 38:37.064
[sighs]
Oh, no.

38:37.099 --> 38:39.700
Madison, I'm living with Tom
at the Bowman's guest house.

38:41.637 --> 38:43.271
No, you're not.

38:43.305 --> 38:44.338
What?

38:44.373 --> 38:47.208
I'll call you back.
[beeps]

38:48.143 --> 38:50.211
[sighs]

38:50.245 --> 38:51.679
Oh, my head.

38:51.713 --> 38:54.015
You can't live here.
Why not?

38:54.049 --> 38:56.350
Because my mom already said
you can't live with us,

38:56.385 --> 38:58.452
and when she finds out
you gave Tom pot brownies,

38:58.487 --> 39:00.221
she's probably gonna
have you arrested.

39:00.255 --> 39:02.690
I didn't know, all right?
They were in the freezer.

39:02.724 --> 39:05.860
So was the ice.
You didn't eat that.
What?

39:05.894 --> 39:08.563
Just get up, okay? Get out.
You cannot stay here.

39:08.597 --> 39:11.732
I have to stay here, Grace.
I have no place else to go.

39:14.136 --> 39:17.371
[chuckles]
You're pathetic,
do you know that?

39:17.406 --> 39:19.073
Yeah, I know that.

39:20.509 --> 39:23.878
[groaning]

39:23.912 --> 39:25.546
[exhales forcefully]

39:25.581 --> 39:28.649
Come on. I really need
somewhere to live.

39:28.684 --> 39:31.519
And Tom needs someone
to live with and...

39:31.553 --> 39:34.789
So will you just help me out
and not say anything
for a few more days?

39:34.823 --> 39:38.693
[sighs]
Well, I guess.

39:38.727 --> 39:41.429
I mean, this was
kind of my dad's hideout,

39:41.463 --> 39:43.431
and I know he would
want this for Tom,

39:43.465 --> 39:46.233
so I won't say anything
to my mom for a few days.

39:46.268 --> 39:49.303
But no more pot brownies
or any other illegal substance.

39:49.338 --> 39:51.005
Got it.

40:06.221 --> 40:08.289
Let's just forget
that happened.

40:09.491 --> 40:11.292
Let's not.

40:12.427 --> 40:14.495
All right.

40:23.972 --> 40:26.073
You could've told us
before now.

40:26.108 --> 40:28.976
I wouldn't have told you now,
but I need to talk to someone.

40:29.011 --> 40:31.712
I can't talk to my dad anymore.
I just can't.

40:31.747 --> 40:34.115
You must be going through hell,
and Adrian, too.

40:34.149 --> 40:35.850
I'm really sorry
you're going through this.

40:35.884 --> 40:37.151
It's more Adrian.

40:37.185 --> 40:38.753
Adrian's
going through this.

40:38.787 --> 40:41.322
Are you gonna go with her?
She doesn't want me
to be there.

40:41.356 --> 40:44.659
She probably just doesn't
wanna ask you to be there.

40:44.693 --> 40:48.029
And you two,
this is not something
that goes beyond this room.

40:48.063 --> 40:49.930
Got it?
[both]
Got it.

40:49.965 --> 40:52.199
I'm gonna go hang out
with Ruben.

40:53.435 --> 40:55.202
Well, he's by himself
with no one to talk to.

40:55.237 --> 40:56.537
Wanna come with me?

40:56.571 --> 40:58.172
Me? No.

40:58.240 --> 41:00.408
You want me to tell you again
where I think you should be
today?

41:00.442 --> 41:02.009
Please don't.

41:02.044 --> 41:04.211
I think I'm doing
the right thing
by just staying here.

41:04.246 --> 41:06.414
All right.

41:06.448 --> 41:09.183
I'll be back later.
You know when.

41:12.854 --> 41:15.289
Whoa, dude.
Bad move calling us over here.

41:15.323 --> 41:17.191
You better get to wherever
Adrian and her mom are.

41:17.225 --> 41:19.527
I don't know about that.
I don't know that
I'd want company.

41:19.561 --> 41:21.996
That could be part
of our hypothetical discussion.

41:22.030 --> 41:25.466
But, Ben, my friend,
this is not hypothetical.

41:25.500 --> 41:27.068
If Adrian's dad's not going

41:27.102 --> 41:28.736
and her mom's just sitting
there by herself--

41:28.770 --> 41:30.438
I don't know--
shouldn't you go?

41:30.472 --> 41:32.039
There is no good decision.

41:32.074 --> 41:33.741
Neither choice
is a good choice.

41:33.775 --> 41:35.376
You're right.
And that's where Adrian is.

41:35.410 --> 41:37.978
She had to make a choice,
and neither one probably
felt like a good one.

41:38.013 --> 41:41.415
All I could do
is just be there.

41:41.450 --> 41:42.717
Exactly.

41:48.990 --> 41:51.726
Okay, Ruben,
we'll see you later.

41:52.828 --> 41:54.628
All right.

41:54.663 --> 41:57.264
I'll see you later, Adrian.
I love you.

41:57.299 --> 41:58.199
Really?

41:58.233 --> 42:01.602
Of course.
I'm your dad.

42:01.636 --> 42:04.538
And even though
I don't want you to do this,

42:04.573 --> 42:06.741
you and your mother are right.

42:06.775 --> 42:09.276
This is your decision.

42:09.311 --> 42:13.414
Just...feel free
to change your mind.

42:15.016 --> 42:16.250
I had to say it.

42:17.686 --> 42:21.021
And I have to say this, too.

42:21.056 --> 42:23.090
I love you, Cindy,

42:23.125 --> 42:25.259
and you've been
a really good mother to Adrian.

42:27.195 --> 42:30.631
So, if I said anything
that implied otherwise,

42:30.665 --> 42:32.266
I'm really sorry.

42:33.835 --> 42:36.003
And I guess being a family

42:36.037 --> 42:38.906
doesn't necessarily mean
we have to agree on everything,

42:38.940 --> 42:41.275
not even the most basic
fundamental things.

42:43.178 --> 42:49.483
And, uh, do you want me
to come with you?

42:49.518 --> 42:52.119
No, but thanks, Dad.

42:53.889 --> 42:55.456
I love you, too.

